    What is a milk carton called?
    They are easy to recognize and are available in two typesshelf-stable (also known as an aseptic carton) and refrigerated (also known as a gable top carton). Cartons are mainly made from paper in the form of paperboard, as well as thin layers of polyethylene (plastic).

    About Cartons - Carton Council of Canada


    Carton Council of Canada
    https://recyclecartons.ca cartons-101
    Carton Council of Canada
    https://recyclecartons.ca cartons-101
    What does 1 carton mean?
    A carton is a box or container usually made of liquid packaging board, paperboard and sometimes of corrugated fiberboard. Many types of cartons are used in packaging. Sometimes a carton is also called a box.

    Carton - Wikipedia


    Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia
    https://en.wikipedia.org wiki Carton
    Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia
    https://en.wikipedia.org wiki Carton
    Is it a carton or box?
    An AI Overview is not available for this searchCan't generate an AI overview right now. Try again later.
    AI Overview
    A carton is a container made from thinner paperboard, often for retail products like cereal or milk. A box is a broader term for a container, but in the context of packaging, it typically refers to a sturdier, multi-layered container made of corrugated cardboard designed for shipping and durability. The main differences are the material thickness and the intended use: cartons are for retail/primary packaging, while boxes are for heavy-duty shipping/secondary packaging.
     
    You can watch this video to learn about the differences between cardboard and carton:

    History of Simple Things
    YouTube 09-Aug-2025
    Carton
    • Material: Thinner paperboard.
    • Structure: Usually a single layer of material.
    • Use: Primarily for retail packaging to protect products and display branding, like in cereal or cosmetic boxes. 
    Box
    • Material: Thicker, multi-layered corrugated cardboard. 
    • Structure: Features an inner and outer layer with a ruffled (fluted) layer in between for strength. 
    • Use: Designed for durability and shipping, ideal for moving or sending products in bulk.
